.TH SUTURE-MERGE_FILE "1" "April 2026" "Suture v5.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
suture\-merge\-file \- Perform three\-way file merge
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B suture merge\-file [\\fIoptions\\fR] \\fIbase\\fR \\fIours\\fR \\fItheirs\\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
Perform three\-way file merge.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \\\-o, \\\-\\\-output \\fI<path>\\fR
Write merged result to a file instead of stdout
.TP
.BR \\\-\\\-driver \\fI<driver>\\fR
Use a semantic merge driver (json, yaml, toml, csv, xml, markdown, docx, xlsx, pptx)
.TP
.BR \\\-\\\-label\-ours \\fI<label>\\fR
Label for "ours" side in conflict markers
.TP
.BR \\\-\\\-label\-theirs \\fI<label>\\fR
Label for "theirs" side in conflict markers
.TP
.BR \\\-C \\fI<REPO_PATH>\\fR
Run as if suture was started in <path>
.TP
.BR \\\-h, \\\-\\\-help
Print help
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
suture merge\-file base.txt ours.txt theirs.txt
suture merge\-file \\\-\\\-driver json base.json ours.json theirs.json
suture merge\-file \\\-\\\-driver yaml \\\-o merged.yaml base.yaml ours.yaml theirs.yaml
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR suture (1)
